definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah  living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.2.42; 
 son of: Mareshah@1Ch.2.42 (H4337); 
 father of: Korah (H7141J), Tappuah (H8599A), Rekem (H7552I), Shema (H8087)
 § Hebron = "association"
1) the 3rd son of Kohath and grandson of Levi
2) a descendant of Caleb
